<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="24" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,639,911,1729]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,290,1496,1517]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named in honor of C. L. Bellamy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,639,911,1729]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,287,1549,1570]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Discussion.</emphasis>
This species is closer to 
<taxonomicName box="[531,638,1549,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Hylaeogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis box="[531,638,1549,1570]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">H. capitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Obenberger 1937:" authorityYear="1344" box="[231,356,1576,1597]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Hylaeogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculum">
<emphasis box="[231,356,1576,1597]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">H. speculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from the former species in being only inconspicuously rather than conspicuously setose on much of the dorsal surface and having only seven larger, mostly truncate teeth on the last abdominal ventrite, rather than about a dozen smaller acute teeth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
